Ag@NCDots/PEDOT:PSS/PVA nanocomposites were successfully designed by using the casting approach for the thermoelectric power applications for the first time. The decoration of the Ag on the NCDots surface has been confirmed by various techniques such as XRD, TEM, FTIR, Raman and XPS. BET analysis proves that Ag@NCDots nanoparticles have a large surface area of 496 m2/g, a typical IV isotherm and their surfaces contain meso and macro-pores which help in the adsorption of organic PEDOT:PSS/PVA molecules and hence reducing the thermal conductivity. The in plane σ

   //
and through plane σ
⊥ values increased with increasing Ag@NCDots. It was found the σ

   //
= 287.4 ± 19 S/cm is due to the well-packed of PEDOT nano-crystals in the films and σ
⊥ = 181.7 ± 11 S/cm at (8 wt% of Ag@NCDots) due to the creation of conductive paths inside the films and the increase in carrier mobility and carrier concentration. Also, Ag@NCDots/PEDOT:PSS/PVA nano-composite shows that the increase in k

