   //
. However, the nanocomposite displayed a high ZT value either in plane or through plane, which gives these materials the opportunity to be good thermoelectrics. 12 legs flexible thermoelectric generator has been engineered with the ability to produce voltage (V

   output
) of 15.12 mV at a ΔT = 16 K. Also the generator exhibited a direct response and linear sensitivity to ΔT. Also, Young's modulus and tensile strength of Ag@NCDots/PEDOT:PSS/PVA films increased with increasing Ag@NCDots concentrations, whereas strain at break decreased gradually due to the increase in the cross-linking densities inside the nanocomposite. The obtained data confirm that the resultant Ag@NCDots/PEDOT:PSS/PVA nano-composite represents a great chance for the future industrial applications in the field of thermal sensors and smart thermoelectric power devices.
